The 2019-20 coronavirus pandemic is an ongoing pandemic of coronavirus disease 2019 (COVID-19), caused by coronavirus 2 associated with severe acute respiratory syndrome (SARS-COV-2).
An outbreak in Wuhan, China, was identified in December 2019, declared a public health emergency of international concern on 30 January 2020, and recognized as a pandemic on 11 March 2020.
