Authorities around the world are responding to this threat by imposing travel restrictions, quarantines, curfews, workplace risk controls and closing facilities.
This pandemic has led to severe global social and economic turmoil, the postponement or cancellation of sporting, religious, political, and cultural events, and a widespread shortage of supplies exacerbated by a panic over purchases.
Schools and universities were closed either nationally or locally in 193 countries, affecting about 99.4 percent of the world’s student population.
