As a result of reduced travel and closure rates for heavy industry, there has been a reduction in air pollution and carbon emissions.
Health authorities in Wuhan (the capital of Hubei Province) China reported a range of cases of pneumonia for an unknown cause on December 31, 2019, and investigation began in early January 2020.
