The virus that caused the outbreak is known as SARS-CoV-2, a newly discovered virus that is closely related to coronaviruses in bats, coronaviruses in squamous antlers, and SARS-CoV. It was later discovered that the first person to show symptoms was clearly infected on 1 December 2019.
