Too much hand washing is also often seen as a symptom of OCD.
There are five essential moments during the day when hand-washing with soap is important to reduce the transmission of diseases through the oral anal route: after using the bathroom (pissing, defecation), after cleaning the baby’s back (changing diapers), before feeding the baby, before eating, before/after preparing food or dealing with raw meat, fish or poultry.
The correct handwashing method should be practiced in other cases in order to prevent the transmission of the disease, such as before or after cutting or wound treatment, after sneezing, coughing or cleaning your nose, after touching or handling animal litter, and after touching rubbish.
In many countries, the rate of handwashing with soap is low.
